President Barack Obama has proclaimed November 2014 as National College Application Month. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of education and equal opportunity for all. It encourages students, regardless of their background or circumstances, to apply to college and pursue higher education. The administration has implemented various programs and resources to make college more affordable and accessible, including grants, tax credits, and loans. Tools like the College Scorecard and Financial Aid Shopping Sheet have been developed to help students and families make informed decisions about college choices and financial aid options. The proclamation also recognizes the efforts of teachers, school counselors, parents, and institutions in supporting students' college aspirations. President Obama calls upon public officials, educators, parents, and all Americans to observe the month with activities and programs that encourage students to plan for and apply to college.